(1, 1, 'A2', 'A2 Foundation', 'A2 is a Foundation Course', 'a2.jpg', '<p>If you are struggling with the basics of English language, you are probably in A1 territory. Prescribed by CEFR (Common European Framework Reference) and designed by BARC, A1 expects you to greet, write an email, or have a telephone conversation in English. At the end of this level, you’ll feel a boost in your communicative abilities. </p> <p>A1 expects you to greet, write an email, or have a telephone conversation in English. At the end of this level, you’ll feel a boost in your communicative abilities. . </p> <h1>Program Benefits</h1> <p> </p> <ul>\r\n                                    <li>You will be able to use familiar everyday expressions and very basic phrases</li>\r\n                                    <li>You will be able to pronounce the words properly</li>\r\n                                    <li>You will be able to ask and answer simple questions in areas of immediate need or on very familiar topics</li>\r\n                                    <li>You will be able to use simple phrases and senteces to describe where you live and people you know</li>\r\n                                    <li>You will be able to write short, simple messages, for example sending holiday greetings</li>\r\n                                    <li>You will have the knowledge of elementary grammar and its use and practice in speaking</li>\r\n                                </ul>', 'A2 is a Foundation Course', 'IELTS student', NULL, NULL),
